<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-758] startHighWaterMarksCheckPointThread is never called</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-758</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;startHighWaterMarksCheckPointThread is never called during startup and hence we only persist the highwater mark file on a clean shutdown. With an unclean shutdown, the highwater marks are not persisted. This causes long recovery time for replicas after unclean shutdowns.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
